def: A small copper coin of Spain, equal to three mils Americanmoney, less than a farthing sterling. Also, an ancient Spanish goldcoin.
One of the three classes into which the fungi are divided inBrefeld's classification. -- Mes`o*my*ce"tous (#), a.
One who inquires or examines; questioner; investigator. Locke.Expert inquirers after truth. Cowper.
A deformity in which the urethra opens upon the top of thepenis, instead of at its extremity.

A black substance; -- formerly applied to various preparationsof a black or very dark color. [Written also Æthiops.] [Obs.] Ethiopsmartial (Old Chem.), black oxide of iron.-- Ethiops mineral (Old Chem.), black sulphide of mercury, obtainedby triturating mercury with sulphur.-- Ethiops per se (Old Chem.), mercury in finely divided state,having the appearance of a dark powder, obtained by shaking it up orby exposure to the air.
Resembling erysipelas, or partaking of its nature.
A ventral canal or groove, in which the males of some dioecioustrematodes carry the female. See Illust. of Hæmatozoa.

A variety of water-tube boiler, used chiefly in steamautomobiles, consisting of a nest of strong tubes with very littlewater space, kept nearly red hot so that the water as it tricklesdrop by drop into the tubes is immediately flashed into steam andsuperheated.
A retiring of the sea, occasioning a change of high-water mark,whereby land is gained.
To inform, fill, or animate, excessively. [R.] Johnson.
Feeding on horseflesh; -- said of certain nomadic tribes, asthe Tartars.
